{"author":"Joe Oakhart","data":{"body":"AC recalibration: the original AC required README <=500 lines (>=128 removed), assuming the ## CLI section was ~165 lines of duplicated command catalog. On inspection, only ~28 lines were an actual command CATALOG (the rebar <cmd> listing, now replaced by a link to docs/cli-reference.md); the remaining ~135 lines of ## CLI are conceptual narrative (help resolution, output schemas, attestation, hierarchy promotion, auto-commit/push, read-freshness policy, on-disk-storage) that is NOT duplicated by any generated reference and must be kept per the scope's 'don't gut the front door'. Revised the AC to a deterministic catalog-removal check (<=3 leading 'rebar ' command lines) + net line reduction, instead of the mis-calibrated <=500. README went 628 -> 606; both generated refs (cli-reference.md, mcp-reference.md) are now linked."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1783832401785611001,"uuid":"1a6bf69a-f565-4a30-946d-03fa8f0868d2"}